    {
      "name": "Description",
      "content": "<p>It's best to know the specific requirements for your state.</p><ul><li>Many states are adopting Sick Accruals for their employees. The requirements may vary from state to state as to what an employee is entitled to.</li><li>Some States allow options which can include entering a flat amount of units at the beginning of a year or \"Front loaded\", or allowing the Sick Accrual pay to be earned on every check.</li><li>If Earned on every check or \"Accrued\", formulas can be used so that a calculation is made so that a set amount is earned depending upon the Total Hrs worked on each check.</li><li>Accrued paid sick leave may be allowed to carry over to the following year of employment and may be capped at a certain amount.</li></ul>"
    },
    {
      "name": "Cause",
      "content": ""
    },
    {
      "name": "Resolution",
      "content": "<p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span><span style=\"color: black;\"><strong>You can choose to enter a flat amount of sick hours for your employees annually. If you choose this option, you'll enter the flat amount of hours every year at the beginning of your payroll year.</strong></span></span></span></span></span></p> <ol style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif;\"> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Set up a new Pay ID for the accrued sick time:</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list 1.0in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>From the Payroll <strong>Setup</strong> menu, select <strong>Pays.</strong></span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list 1.0in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Enter a <strong>Pay ID</strong> \"CA SICK\" and <strong>Description</strong></span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list 1.0in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Select <strong>Accrual</strong> from the <strong>Pay Type</strong> drop down list.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list 1.0in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Clear all <strong>Distribute to</strong> check boxes.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list 1.0in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Select <strong>Flat Amount</strong> from the <strong>Calculation method</strong> drop down list.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list 1.0in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Do not select the <strong>Retain YTD totals at close year</strong> check box. You will be Front loading your sick hours every year.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list 1.0in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Select the <strong>Units</strong> check box.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list 1.0in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Click <strong>Save</strong>, then <strong>Close</strong>.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> </ol> <p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list 1.0in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Enter the required number of units by using one of the methods found in the article below.</span></span></span></span></span></span></strong></p> <p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\">&nbsp;</p> <p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span><span style=\"color: black;\">You can choose to accrue sick units based on hours worked. For the specifics on how to create this formula, see the article below. \\</span></span></span></strong></span></span></p> <p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\">&nbsp;</p> <ol style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif;\"> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Create a <strong>TOTAL HOURS</strong> formula that contains the following fields and parameters:<br>Regular Hours[PR Check] + Overtime Hours[PR Check]</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> </ol> <ol style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif;\" start=\"2\"> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Create the <strong>SICK ACCR</strong> formula that contains the following fields and parameters:</span></span></span></span></span></span><br><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span><span style=\"color: black;\">TOTAL HOURS[Public Formula]/30</span></span></span></span></span></li> </ol> <p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\"><br><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span><span style=\"color: black;\"><strong>Note</strong>: To accrue 1 hour of sick time for every 30 hours worked, the basis is the TOTAL HOURS formula, the rate is 1/30th of an hour per hour worked.</span></span></span></span></span></p> <ul style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif;\"> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>If an employee works 15 hours, they accrue .5 hours of sick time. If they work 30 hours, they accrue 1 hour. If they work 60 hours, they accrue 2 hours.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>If the employee works 10 hours 1 week, 10 hours the next week, and 10 hours the third week the total they will have accrued a total of 1 hour for the 30 hours worked.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> </ul> <p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\"><strong>Create your Pay id's.&nbsp; This workflow assumes you are rolling over Sick earned and Sick taken pay id's when you close the year in Payroll.</strong></p> <p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\">&nbsp;</p> <p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span><span style=\"color: black;\">Set up a new Pay ID for the accrued sick time earned:</span></span></span></strong></span></span></p> <ol style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif;\"> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>From the Payroll <strong>Setup</strong> menu, select <strong>Pays.</strong></span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Enter a <strong>Pay ID</strong> \"CA SICK\" and <strong>Description. Note: Your description will vary based on your state and pay id.</strong></span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Select <strong>Accrual</strong> from the <strong>Pay Type</strong> drop down list.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Clear all <strong>Distribute to</strong> check boxes.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Select <strong>Formula</strong> from the <strong>Calculation method</strong> drop down list.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Select the <strong>SICK ACCR</strong> in the <strong>Formula</strong> field.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Select the <strong>Retain YTD totals at close year</strong> check box.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Select the <strong>Units</strong> check box.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Click <strong>Save</strong>, then <strong>Close</strong>.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>From the <strong>Setup</strong> menu, select <strong>Employees</strong>.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Select the employee and click <strong>Pays</strong>.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Enter the <strong>Pay ID</strong> you set up in step 3 above.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Select the <strong>Auto</strong> check box.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> </ol><p style=\"margin: 0in; font-size: 14.6667px; letter-spacing: 0.2px; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\">Set up a new Pay ID for the accrued sick time taken:</span></span></span></span></p><ol style=\"font-size: 14.6667px; letter-spacing: 0.2px; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif;\"><li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">From the Payroll&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Setup</span>&nbsp;menu, select&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Pays.</span></span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Enter a&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Pay ID</span>&nbsp;\"CASICK TKN\" and&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Description. Note: Your description will vary based on your state and pay id.</span></span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Select&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Accrual</span>&nbsp;from the&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Pay Type</span>&nbsp;drop down list.</span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Clear all&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Distribute to</span>&nbsp;check boxes.</span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Select <strong>Other Units</strong>&nbsp;from the&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Calculation method</span>&nbsp;drop down list.</span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Select the&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Retain YTD totals at close year</span> check box.</span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Select the&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Units</span> check box.</span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Click&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Save</span>, then&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Close</span>.</span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">This pay is used when entering Sick paid Units.&nbsp; Using this pay and entering units will cause the pay you are setting up below to calculate an amount.&nbsp;</span></span></span></li></ol> <p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\">&nbsp;</p> <p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span><span style=\"color: black;\">Set up a new Pay ID to pay the employee for sick time:</span></span></span></strong></span></span></p> <ol> <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>From the Payroll <strong>Setup</strong> menu, select <strong>Pays</strong>.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Enter the new <strong>Pay ID</strong> \"SICK\" and <strong>Description</strong> for the sick pay. <strong>Note: Your description will vary based on your state and pay id.</strong></span></span></span></span></span></span></li> <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>Select <strong>Other</strong> from the <strong>Pay Type</strong> drop down list.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li><li style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span>The Calculation Method will be <strong>Formula.&nbsp; You will use a formula which looks at the units you've entered for the CASICK TKN accrual pay and multiply those units by the regular rate of pay for the employee.&nbsp; Formula is below \"SICK RATE\".</strong></span></span></span></span></span></span></li><li style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Do NOT Select the <span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Retain YTD totals at close year</span>&nbsp;check box for this pay id.</span></span></span></li><li style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Setup the following formulas:&nbsp; The Pay Id listed within the quotes is the exact Pay id, you've setup.</span></span></span></li><li style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">The rate formula is an example of a formula which retrieves a specific rate of pay, for additional Rate formula examples see the linked article below.</span></span></span></li><li style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">This pay id should be added to the employee pay record and the automatic check box should be selected.&nbsp; When units are entered for pay id \"CASICK TKN\", this pay should automatically process on the check.&nbsp; NOTE:&nbsp; Always test your setup.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span></li></ol><p><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">VAC/Sick Rate Formula:</span></span></span></p><ul><li style=\"\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">LOOKUP(Amount[PR Employee Pay],Employee([PR Check],1,\"REG\")﻿-This formula is used within the formula below:</span></span></span></li></ul><p style=\"\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">SICK PAID formula:</span></span></span></p><ul><li style=\"\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">IF(Pay ID[PR Time]=\"CASICK TKN\",Units[PR Time]*VAC/Sick Rate Formula[Public Formula]) This formula is placed on the SICK Pay you've setup.&nbsp;</span></span></span></li></ul><p style=\"\"><span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.2px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: black; display: inline !important;\">For additional formula examples see: </span>[[How do I set up an Other pay that retrieves a rate of pay?|223924350034205]]<br></p> <p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span><span style=\"color: black;\">Create and add the following formula to the check stub to show the sick pay balance for the employee</span></span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span><span style=\"color: black;\">:</span></span></span></span></span></p> <p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span><span style=\"color: black;\">SICK BALANCE:</span></span></span></span></span></p> <p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span><span style=\"color: black;\">(Lookup(YTD Units[PR Employee Pay], Employee[PR Check],5,\"CA SICK\")-Lookup(YTD Units(PR Employee Pay),Employee(PR Check),5,\"CASICK PD\"))/8<br><br><strong>Note:</strong> This formula returns the number of sick days the employee had available, as required by the law.</span></span></span></span></span></p> <p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span><span style=\"color: black;\">The specific pay id you created will be within the Quotations.</span></span></span></span></span></p> <p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span><span style=\"color: black;\">For more information on how to add the formula to the Check stub see the article below</span></span></span></span></span></p>"
    },
